## Event Overview

Legendary Release Events are multi-track events where players earn points by completing battles with teams that satisfy specific requirements.

## Event Goal

The goal is to earn enough points to unlock the featured Legendary character.

Progress carries over between appearances, so every point matters even if you do not unlock the character during the current event.

## Requirements and Tracks

Each event is divided into multiple tracks with different enemy types and team-building restrictions.

Common requirements include:

* Faction restrictions
* Damage type restrictions
* Trait restrictions
* Rarity or character limitations
* Survival-based scoring

## Team Planning

Strong teams usually either stack multiple requirements at once or focus on high-value single requirements with reliable characters.

This guide prioritizes practical teams that newer and mid-game players are more likely to build and survive with.

## Long-Term Strategy

Legendary Release Events reward preparation.

Investing in flexible characters, healers, durable tanks, and commonly reused damage types can improve performance across multiple future events.
